            "description": "",
            "details": "<p class=\"p1\"><em>Sermīn</em>: It is a small town belonging to the the districts of Aleppo. In former times it had around three hundred mosques, and prayers were performed in all of them. At present, only one mosque remains in which the prayers are performed. Most of its people were <em>İsma‘īliyye</em> (Ismā‘īlīs). After some time, when the Tatar army took control, their order and community were disrupted. [translation]</p>",
            "end": 1599,
